 Development Manual
====================

http://github.com/svenfuchs/gem-release

   mv flickru /tmp # flickru is generated by bundle
                   # unfortunately, bump tries to bump versions inside it too
   gem bump --version (major|minor|patch) # upgrade version with jeweler 
   mv /tmp/flickru .

http://gembundler.com

   gem install bundler

   bundle install        # update Gemfile.lock against Gemfile changes
   bundle update [<gem>] # update Gemfile & Gemfile.lock for gem/s upgrade
                         # ... needed if install fail due to unresolved dependencies
   git add Gemfile Gemfile.lock # add changes to git

   bundle exec [app params...]           # execute bundled app
   bundle exec rspec spec/flickru_spec:N # execute rspec line N

http://github.com/technicalpickles/jeweler

   gem install jeweler
   rake -T             # show options

   # initialisation
   jeweler my-new-project
   git remote rm origin
   git remote add origin git@github.com:jesuspv/my-new-project.git
   rake version:write MAJOR=0 MINOR=0 PATCH=0 # set initial version
   rake gemspec                               # create project gemspec
   git add -A                                 # git: add changes to already-managed files
   git commit -a -m "initial commit"          # git: commit all updated or removed files
   rake release                               # initial release, push to GitHub and rubygems

   rake version:bump:(major|minor|patch) # upgrade version
   rake gemspec                          # !!?? copied from:
                                         # www.cerebris.com/blog/2011/03/15/creating-and-managing-private-rubygems-with-jeweler-github-and-bundler/
   git commit -a -m "made some changes"
   rake release
